channel.title: Odd update (rollback to previous version)
channel.description:
I was just grepping my update log: https://www.moparisthebest.com/rs/update.log
And discovered an interesting update:
[code]#590 update of runescape.jar occured 02-11-10_09 md5sum: 6cb028fc1e5a36c7a13ccf4128f1d064 Last update of loader.jar occured 02-11-10_09 md5sum: 725508e27aaf225d7b716f340acfd739 #591 update of runescape.jar occured 02-16-10_09 md5sum: eb67a5060b2894ba30e96e6c5c26ad7d Last update of loader.jar occured 02-16-10_09 md5sum: 9258f50a5d2bd4ba415794ff41cade6f #590 update of runescape.jar occured 02-22-10_09 md5sum: 6cb028fc1e5a36c7a13ccf4128f1d064 Last update of loader.jar occured 02-22-10_09 md5sum: 725508e27aaf225d7b716f340acfd739 #592 update of runescape.jar occured 02-22-10_10 md5sum: 75ab615ffd9a29907e522f1923465100 Last update of loader.jar occured 02-22-10_10 md5sum: b1639c36277ee9dc91f4e322d0dbfe23 [/code]
Yes it's slightly more than a year ago, but still interesting.
Basically, they released 590, 5 days later released 591, 6 days later released the same 590 AGAIN, and less than an hour later released 592. Now either a big mistake was discovered in 591 they had to quickly disable, or they somehow accidentally released 590 again, which is unlikely.
Anyone want to look up what exactly was going on at this time? Was it a bugfix from 591? It's interesting to me anyhow. :)
